						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken stone built into the wall of the backyard of the house of Sōmangauḍa Dyāvanagauḍar.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12-13th century A.D.</hi> seems to record a grant of land made by the potter <hi rend="bold">Mādhava,</hi> in the presence of the <hi rend="italic">Ūroḍeya</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> town <hi rend="bold">Hattiyamattavūr.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
